content:
Most Voice telephony partners provide a managed package that contains the metadata to connect Voice with the partner’s system. Download the package from AppExchange or ask your telephony provider for the installation URL.

To view the Partner Telephony Setup page: Customize Application.
To install packages: Download AppExchange Packages.

This task applies to this telephony model:

SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

Most telephony partners provide a managed package that contains the following:

Connector in the form of a Visualforce page
Visualforce page name
Package’s namespace that is used to create a contact center

Telephony partners provide their own documentation for their managed package.

From Setup, enter Partner Telephony Setup in the Quick Find box, then select Partner Telephony Setup.
Click Go to AppExchange.
Search for your telephony partner’s package and follow its installation instructions.

After you install the managed package, check that all of the components were installed. Ask your telephony provider for instructions to verify that the components were installed properly.
title: Installing Telephony Provider's Managed Package
